<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES60-5 - DISASSEMBLE - SHIFT
        TOWER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SHIFT TOWER</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301202">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301202" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301202" filename="../figg13/G1301202.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 2. Shift Tower</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HANDLE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. LEVER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SPRING RETAINER LOCK PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SPRING</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>6. BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>7. ROCK SHAFT PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>8. GASKET</callout1>
                <callout1>9. LEVER HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>10. SNAP RING</callout1>
                <callout1>11. LEVER COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>12. SPRING RETAINER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts and lockwashers. Separate the lever housing from the shifter
                housing and gasket. Lift it straight up.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position shift lever housing on edge in a vise.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press the spring retainer against the spring. Remove the lock pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide lever cover up the shift lever and remove the rock shaft snap ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tap the rock shaft free of the lever housing and remove the shift lever. Remove and discard
                the gasket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shift lever handle. Slide lever cover, spring retainer and spring off the
                lever.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wash all parts thoroughly and inspect the lever and rock shaft cross holes (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301203">Figure 3</hotlnk>) for excessive wear. Replace all worn or damaged parts.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301203" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301203" filename="../figg13/G1301203.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Inspect Cross Holes</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check spring tension by comparing the old spring to a new one. Replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
